<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="204" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/2599½</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The British Chargé</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Barclay</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 913</seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-16">
                                <hi rend="italic">August 16, 1918</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have the honour to inform
                        you that, in reply to a note from the Japanese Ambassador, His Majesty’s
                        Government have accepted the view of the Japanese Government—so far as
                        British troops are concerned—that the Supreme Command of the Allied forces
                        operating in Siberia and based on the Pacific should be Japanese.</p>
                    <p>The Japanese Ambassador has been further informed that General Knox will be
                        head of the British Military Mission attached to the staff of the Japanese
                        Commander-in-Chief.</p>
                    <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Colville Barclay</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>